#compdef ttl
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ttl — fast, modern traceroute with real-time TUI, per-hop stats,
#       ASN/geo lookup, ECMP detection, and MPLS label parsing —
#       a better mtr (Rust, 1,032★)
#
# upstream: https://github.com/lance0/ttl
# author : Lance0 (lance0)
# license: MIT OR Apache-2.0 (dual)
#
# Source-direct completion: every flag below is verbatim from src/cli.rs
# on the lance0/ttl v0.19.1 tip — clap-derive `Args` struct with `#[arg(
# short, long, default_value, conflicts_with, requires, value_parser)]`
# attributes parsed exactly as declared.
#
# Direct deps from Cargo.toml (selected):
#   hickory-resolver  0.26    ← canonical Rust pure-Rust DNS library
#                              (this axis) — by Benjamin Fry (bluejekyll)
#                              + the Hickory DNS collective (formerly
#                              "trust-dns" until the 2024 rename to
#                              avoid trademark issues with the Trust-
#                              Domain naming).  Pure-Rust DNS stub
#                              resolver + recursive resolver + authoritative
#                              server + protocol implementation; the
#                              only full DNS toolkit in Rust without
#                              shelling out to libc's getaddrinfo.
#                              Used by Quinn (QUIC), reqwest (when
#                              `hickory-dns` feature enabled), Linkerd
#                              proxy, Pingora-rs, and ttl (this CLI).
#   pnet              0.35    (Robert Clipsham's libpnet — packet
#                              manipulation, raw sockets, Ethernet/IP/
#                              TCP/UDP/ICMP packet types)
#   socket2           0.6     (low-level socket extensions)
#   ratatui + crossterm       (TUI rendering)
#   reqwest                   (HTTP for PeeringDB IX lookups)
#   maxminddb         0.27    (MaxMind GeoLite2 ASN+City database
#                              reader)
#   ipnetwork                 (IPv4/IPv6 CIDR utilities)
#   clap (derive) + clap_complete (CLI parser)
#   tokio (full) + tokio-util + futures (async runtime)
#   chrono                    (export timestamps)
#
# ttl is a modern mtr/traceroute replacement that combines per-hop RTT
# tracking, multi-flow ECMP path discovery, IX (Internet Exchange)
# detection via PeeringDB, ASN/geolocation enrichment via MaxMind
# GeoLite2, MPLS label parsing, path MTU discovery, DSCP QoS testing,
# detection indicators for NAT/rate-limiting/asymmetric routing/TTL
# manipulation, and a ratatui-based TUI with 11 themes (default,
# kawaii, cyber, dracula, monochrome, matrix, nord, gruvbox,
# catppuccin, tokyo_night, solarized).  DNS lookups for reverse-DNS,
# ASN lookups for AS numbers, and PeeringDB queries all route through
# `hickory-resolver` (with `--no-dns` / `--no-asn` / `--no-geo` /
# `--no-ix` flags to skip each individually).  Supports batch CSV /
# JSON / report-mode export with `-c` (count) flag + `--replay`
# of saved sessions with optional `--animate` and `--speed` controls.
#
# === AXIS 178 OPENER — pure-language DNS libraries (resolver+protocol) ===
# Axis position: Rust=233 OPENS Axis 178 at slot 1/0/0.  Canonical Rust
# pure-language DNS library is `hickory-resolver` + the larger Hickory
# DNS toolkit (formerly trust-dns) by Benjamin Fry (bluejekyll); pure-
# Rust DNS stub resolver + recursive resolver + authoritative server +
# protocol message encoding/decoding without shelling out to libc's
# getaddrinfo or system stub resolver.  Renamed from trust-dns to
# hickory-dns in 2024 to avoid trademark friction.  Adopted across the
# Rust networking ecosystem — Quinn (QUIC client/server), reqwest's
# optional resolver backend, Linkerd2 proxy, Pingora-rs, ttl (this
# CLI), and many more.
#
# Cycle position in current 3+1 micro-cycle:
#   Rust=233     ← THIS FILE              (axis 178 OPENS, slot 1/0/0)
#   Go=233       ← next round              (axis 178 continues, slot 2/0/0)
#   TS-Node=233  ← round after             (axis 178 CLOSES at triple-233, slot 1/1/1)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

_ttl() {
    _arguments -s -S \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[print help (with EXAMPLES and DETECTION INDICATORS in after_help)]' \
        '(- *)'{-V,--version}'[print version]' \
        '(-c --count)'{-c,--count=}'[number of probe rounds (0 = infinite, default 0)]:N:' \
        '(-i --interval)'{-i,--interval=}'[probe interval in seconds (default 1.0)]:seconds:' \
        '(-m --max-ttl)'{-m,--max-ttl=}'[maximum TTL hops (default 30)]:hops:' \
        '(-p --protocol)'{-p,--protocol=}'[probe protocol (default auto)]:protocol:(auto icmp udp tcp)' \
        '--port=[port for UDP/TCP probes]:port:' \
        '--fixed-port[use fixed port (disable per-TTL port variation)]' \
        '--flows=[number of flows for multi-path ECMP detection (1 = classic mode, default 1)]:N:' \
        '--src-port=[base source port for flow identification (default 50000)]:port:' \
        '--timeout=[probe timeout in seconds (default 3)]:seconds:' \
        '(-4 --ipv4)'{-4,--ipv4}'[force IPv4]' \
        '(-6 --ipv6)'{-6,--ipv6}'[force IPv6]' \
        '--resolve-all[trace all resolved IP addresses for hostnames (round-robin DNS, dual-stack)]' \
        '--no-dns[skip reverse DNS lookups]' \
        '--no-asn[skip ASN enrichment]' \
        '--no-geo[skip geolocation]' \
        '--no-ix[skip IX detection (PeeringDB)]' \
        '--geoip-db=[path to MaxMind GeoLite2 database file]:GeoIP db:_files -g "*.(mmdb|MMDB)"' \
        '--no-tui[disable TUI (streaming output mode)]' \
        '--json[output JSON (batch mode, requires -c)]' \
        '--csv[output CSV (batch mode, requires -c)]' \
        '--report[report mode (batch, requires -c)]' \
        '--replay=[replay a saved session]:session file:_files -g "*.(json|csv|JSON|CSV)"' \
        '--animate[animate replay showing probe-by-probe discovery (requires --replay)]' \
        '--speed=[replay speed multiplier (1.0 = realtime, default 10.0; requires --animate)]:speed:' \
        '--theme=[color theme (default `default`)]:theme:(default kawaii cyber dracula monochrome matrix nord gruvbox catppuccin tokyo_night solarized)' \
        '--wide[wide mode: expand columns for wider terminals]' \
        '--interface=[bind probes to specific network interface (e.g. eth0, wlan0)]:interface:' \
        '--recv-any[do not bind receiver socket to interface (allows asymmetric routing; requires --interface)]' \
        '--dscp=[DSCP value for QoS testing (0-63; e.g. 46 for VoIP EF)]:DSCP 0-63:' \
        '--size=[probe packet size in bytes (36-9216 IPv4, 56-9216 IPv6; includes IP+protocol headers; conflicts with --pmtud)]:bytes:' \
        '--pmtud[enable Path MTU discovery mode (binary search for max unfragmented size)]' \
        '--jumbo[enable jumbo frame detection (9216 byte max) for PMTUD; without this --pmtud uses standard ethernet max 1500 (requires --pmtud)]' \
        '--rate=[maximum probes per second (0 = unlimited, max 10000)]:N:' \
        '--source-ip=[source IP address for probes]:IP:' \
        '--completions=[generate shell completions and exit]:shell:(bash zsh fish powershell)' \
        '*:target host (IP or hostname; multiple targets allowed):_hosts'
}

_ttl "$@"
